, dendropithecids, and cercopithecoids ( 17 , 38 , 82 ) and more closely resembles Proconsul ( 88 ), although the ulnar head is less extensive than in extant hominoids. In contrast with these derived features, the humeral shaft and humeroulnar joint are plesiomorphic: The former (
